<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Plate Flaking" class="currentChild" href="Plate_Flaking">Plate Flaking</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A printing problem of <a title="Offset Lithography" href="Offset_Lithography">offset lithography</a>, characterized by portions of the image areas of the plate flaking off. Plate flaking is primarily a problem of plates utilizing copper-based coatings that harden in the image areas, forming the ink-receptive portion of the plate. Poor <a title="Adhesion" href="Adhesion">adhesion</a> of the copper layer results in a chipping off of the copper, which can result in the chips adhering to the <a title="Blanket" href="Blanket">blanket</a>, elsewhere on the plate, or in the ink <a title="Roller Train" href="Roller_Train">roller train</a>, which can produce <a title="Hickey" href="Hickey">hickey</a>s or other printing defects. 
</p>
